# Two-level functions + managers

## Layers

| Layer | Path | Imports |
|-------|------|---------|
| Level 1 | `**/functions/**/*.ts` | `import type` from `app/types/**` only. No NPM, no `i18n`, no other project files. Dependencies = function arguments (DI). |
| Level 2 | `**/*_manager.ts`, `src/stores/S_*.ts`, `**/_data/**/*.ts`, IPC registrars | Full wiring: NPM, `src/`, `i18n`, level-1 `functions/`. |
| Vue SFC | `src/components/**`, `src/layouts/**`, `src/pages/**`, `App.vue` | When `scripts/*_manager.ts` exists: only that manager, child `*.vue`, `import type` from `app/types/**`. Template + styles stay in SFC. |

## Manager file naming

Level-2 entry modules: suffix **`_manager.ts`** (underscore before `manager`), not `.manager.ts`. Examples: `dialogAppSettings_manager.ts`, `faKeybindsChordUiFormatting_manager.ts`. Grep `*_manager.ts` to list.

## No re-export shim files

Do **not** add module whose only job is `export { … } from './someOther_manager'` (or old `faFooStore.ts` re-exporting `foo_manager.ts`). Import **real** `*_manager.ts` or `functions/*.ts`. Same inside manager: avoid `export { helper } from './other_manager'` when callers can import `other_manager` / `functions/…` directly. Domain **barrel** files (`keybinds_manager.ts` `export *` from sibling managers) OK as single entry — not legacy alias duplicating one manager under old name.

## Managers are wiring-only (`fa-two-level/manager-wiring-only`)

`*_manager.ts` must **not** define functions (`export function`, inner `function`, top-level `const`/`let` with function expressions, **`class`**). Only **imports** deps, **invokes** factories from `functions/` (or sibling wiring when level-1 cannot import shared deps), **exports `const` bindings** to returned API (e.g. `export const getFaUserSettings = storeApi.get`).

**Allowed:** `export const x = create…({ … })`, `const api = create…({ … })` when initializer is **call** to factory (not top-level arrow/function). **Arrow functions/lambdas inside factory argument object** (e.g. `getInnerHeight: () => window.innerHeight` into `createUseFeature`) OK — nested property values, not top-level manager bodies.

**Not managers:** Stateful **classes**, long-lived sessions, multi-step wiring building `sessionDeps` from `window`/Electron APIs → **sibling modules without `_manager` suffix** (e.g. `faFloatingWindowTitleDragPointerSession.ts`, `faFloatingWindowResizePointerSessionWiring.ts`) or `functions/` when body pure + fully injected. Do **not** name implementation-only module `*_manager.ts` just because manager imports it.

**Renderer wiring siblings:** Level-1 `functions/` cannot import `window`, Pinia, project modules → colocated `*Wiring.ts` (or `*Session.ts` / `*Bound.ts`) next to manager; same as Electron `*Surface.ts` / `*Api.ts` next to `*_manager.ts`.

Composable managers: `export const useFeature = createUseFeature({ ref, computed, i18n, … })` with `createUseFeature` under `functions/`.

## Layout per feature

```
<Feature>/
  Feature.vue
  scripts/
    <feature>_manager.ts
    functions/
      <concern>.ts
```

Shared domains: `src/scripts/<domain>/functions/` + `<domain>/*_manager.ts` (optional `<domain>_manager.ts` barrel). Electron: `src-electron/mainScripts/<area>/functions/` + `*_manager.ts` (public entry) + allowed siblings: `*_managerDefaults.ts`, `*Wiring.ts`, `*Surface.ts`, `*Session.ts`, `*Runtime.ts`, `*Api.ts`, `*Bound.ts`. `ipcManagement/`: `registerFa*Ipc.ts`, `revealElectronDevToolsConsoleBestEffort.ts` = level-2 IPC registrars. `appProtocol/`: `registerFaAppProtocolWiring.ts`. ESLint `fa-two-level/feature-scripts-layout` on `mainScripts/<area>/` like component `scripts/` when `functions/` exists.

## ESLint rule ids (CI)

| Rule | Role |
|------|------|
| `import/no-restricted-paths` (zones) | `functions/` import boundaries; who may import `functions/` |
| `@typescript-eslint/no-restricted-imports` | NPM denylist on `functions/**` |
| `@typescript-eslint/consistent-type-imports` | On `functions/**` |
| `fa-two-level/functions-only-type-imports` | AST fallback for level 1 |
| `fa-two-level/feature-scripts-layout` | If `scripts/functions/` exists, only `*_manager.ts` siblings |
| `fa-two-level/require-manager-when-functions` | Requires `*_manager.ts` when `functions/` exists |
| `fa-two-level/vue-script-import-allowlist` | Thin Vue script when manager exists |
| `fa-two-level/no-functions-import-manager` | Level 1 must not import managers/stores |
| `fa-two-level/stores-functions-layout` | Who may import `src/stores/functions/` |
| `fa-two-level/manager-wiring-only` | `*_manager.ts` no local functions, top-level arrow/function `const`/`let`, or `class` bodies |

Plugin: [eslint-rules/faTwoLevelPlugin.mjs](../../eslint-rules/faTwoLevelPlugin.mjs). Run `yarn lint:eslint` after each migration.

## Exclusions

No two-level rules on: `**/*playwright*`, `helpers/playwrightHelpers_*`, `e2e-tests/`, `i18n/**/*.ts`, `types/**`, configs, `*.vitest.test.ts`, `*.stories.ts`.

